# Trivy ignore list for tesserix base images.
#
# Each entry must document why the CVE is not actionable (upstream only
# patched in HEAD, pkg never reached at runtime, etc.) and a review
# date. Prefer actually fixing the vuln by bumping the base, not
# ignoring it.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CVE-2026-33671 — picomatch Regular Expression Denial of Service
# (GHSA-qmt-xxm8-qqq4).
#
# Affects: every node:22-alpine / node:24-alpine upstream image — they
# bundle corepack + npm which pull picomatch via a transitive that
# declares "picomatch": "^4.0.3" in its package.json. Trivy's npm
# scanner reads the LOWER BOUND of the SemVer range (4.0.3) and flags
# it, even though npm actually resolves to 4.0.4 on disk.
#
# Review trigger: once node:NN-alpine ships a base image where every
# transitive package.json declares ^4.0.4 or newer, drop this entry.
# Last checked: 2026-04-20 (node:22-alpine v22.22.x, node:24-alpine
# v24.15.x) — still carried upstream.
CVE-2026-33671
